cancelTrade(uint256).details: changes the status of the trade to cancelled

returns._0: all true  if trade was cancelled

executeTrade(uint256).details: verifies assets ownership from both parties before swapping them.

getTrade(uint256).details: indexes and returns information about the trade

returns._0: creator address, executor address and trade status

getTradeWithAddress(uint256,address).details: indexes internal sctructure and information based on tradeId and wallet address

params.userWallet: to check trades for that wallet address

returns._0: arrays of tokenAddress, tokenIds, tokenAmount, tokenType

setAssetPerTrade(uint256).details: set max number of asset per trade need to be less then 1000

startTrade(address[],uint256[],uint256[].details: checks if both users own all assets requested by the trade creator and initiates the trade if verification returns true

params.creatorAmount: array containing the amount of each token (only applicable for erc1155 and erc20) to be swapped by the creator
params.creatorTokenAddress: array containing the address of the contract of each asset to be swapped by the creator
params.creatorTokenId: array containing tokenId of each asset (only applicable for erc721 and erc1155) to be swapped by the creator
params.creatorTokenType: array containing the token standard of each asset (erc20, erc721 and erc1155) to be swapped by the creator
params.executorAmount: array containing the amount of each token (only applicable for erc1155 and erc20) to be swapped by the executor
params.executorTokenAddress: array containing the address of the contract of each asset to be swapped by the executor
params.executorTokenId: array containing tokenId of each asset (only applicable for erc721 and erc1155) to be swapped by the executor
params.executorTokenType: array containing the token standard of each asset (erc20, erc721 and erc1155) to be swapped by the executor

returns._0: all trades created by a user

tradePerUser(address).details: returns all trades open for an address stored in the _openTrades index

params.u: to check open trades based on wallet address

returns._0: all trades open for a user

cancelTrade(uint256).notice: cancelTrade -  To invalidate an already created trade. Can be called by both the trade creator or executor

getTrade(uint256).notice: getTrade - this method returns data about the trade based on tradeId

getTradeWithAddress(uint256,address).notice: getTrade - this method returns data about the trade based on tradeId and user wallet

setAssetPerTrade(uint256).notice: Set number of asset per trade

tradePerUser(address).notice: tradePerUser - Returns all open trades for a given wallet address
